news.title: Greater Noida development body to hold builder-wise registry camps
news.para: They added that after getting positive responses from weekly camps held last month, the authority has issued a roaster for facilitating the registry of flats for November.

news.title: Geberit's operating profit fell 26.4% in Q3 2022
news.para: The maker of bathroom piping, ceramics and shower toilets said its sales fell to 790.7 million Swiss francs ($788.33 million)during the three months to the end of September.

news.title: Runwise raises $19 million to improve buildings' energy efficiency
news.para: The Series A financing was also backed by several large real estate owners, including New York's Rudin and SOJA Ventures, the investment arm of the Swig family that owns Halstead and Brown Harris Stevens.

news.title: Rs 4.25 lakh in fines for GRAP violations in Noida
news.para: The Noida Authority said a total of 14 cases of violation of GRAP rules were recorded in which the offenders were penalized.

news.title: Morgan Stanley leases 86,200 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: The financial major will be paying a lease of over Rs 340 crores throughout the lease term for a total 86,200 sq ft office space on 39th and 40th floor of the upcoming tower Altimus being developed by K Raheja Corp.

news.title: Goa: Departments to get 20 days to submit reports on land conversion
news.para: In case these authorities fail to submit their reports to the revenue department within 20 days, the collector concerned will proceed with the land conversion process on the basis of available information.

news.title: Arvind Smartspaces' net profit rises 109% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The board of directors approved the proposal to raise funds by way of issuance of debt securities including but not limited to senior, secured, rated, listed, redeemable non-convertible debentures on private placement basis up to Rs 150 crore.

news.title: YEIDA seeks answers from firms on how to control dust at construction sites
news.para: Officials said they are exploring soil stabilisation methods that can restrict construction dust from flying in the area, a major cause of air pollution especially in the winter season.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's net profit rises 17.41% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 931 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of from Rs 743.90 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Panel to identify dwellings within forest buffer zones in Goa
news.para: ​Once identified, these structures will be incorporated in the Zonal Master Plan (ZMP) of the respective eco-sensitive zone which is being prepared by the town and country planning (TCP) department.

news.title: Maharashtra: Locals may not need CRZ nod for houses up to 3,000 sqft in coastal area
news.para: The state government has made the proposal to the Union ministry for environment, forests and climate change (MoEFCC) while forwarding the draft coastal zone management plans (CZMP) for Palghar, Thane, Sindhudurg, Raigad and Ratnagiri.

news.title: Land documents to be linked to owner's email, phone: Goa law minister
news.para: ​The idea, Cabral said, was to link the land ownership documents with the emails IDs and mobile numbers of the owners, so that they receive an automated alert once any attempt is made to tamper with or sell their properties.

news.title: Nashik civic body restarts playing drums in front of tax defaulters' houses
news.para: NMC teams are visiting the houses of the big tax defaulters and playing drums there. So far, the civic body has collected Rs 5.5 crore from the tax defaulters.

news.title: In demand: 443 applicants for e-auction of 34 plots in Noida
news.para: After the end of the e-auction process, officials found that "exorbitant" and "impractical" bids were made for eight plots, which were as high as 16 times their reserve price.

news.title: GRAP curbs no obstacle to Noida airport construction: Officials
news.para: The greenfield airport is coming up in Jewar, some 75 km off Delhi, along the Yamuna Expressway. The airport is being developed in four phases and the first phase is scheduled to be completed by September 2024.
